A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Kimia Irmesha Flournoy on Women Veterans Appreciation
2 Day at the Capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Kimia Irmesha Flournoy served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and
4 liberty with the United States Marine Corps, valiantly and courageously protecting her fellow
5 Americans from 1998 to 2006; and
6 WHEREAS, during her tenure in the military, she was stationed at seven different bases and
7 was deployed in Norway and Iraq; and
8 WHEREAS, her awards and military decorations include the Presidential Unit Citation (1st
9 FSSG), Global War on Terrorism Expeditionary Medal, Sea Service Deployment Ribbonwith
10 1 star, National Defense Service Medal, Good Conduct Medal, three Meritorious Masts, and
11 three Letters of Appreciation; and
12 WHEREAS, she relocated to metro Atlanta after her departure from the military, where she
13 took on leadership roles in various veteran service organizations such as Commander of
14 American Legion Mundy-Beck Post 9-1-1 for four years, the Atlanta Mobile Food
15 Distribution Coordinator for Soldiers Angels for two years, Team Lead for Minority
