16 Veterans of America (Atlanta Chapter) for two years, Project Coordinator for Society's
17 Gardeners, Team RWB Atlanta Chapter Captain for two years, musician and coach with
18 Alchemy Sky Veterans Music Project, and was The Mission Continues Atlanta 3rd Platoon
19 Leader for three years; and
20 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentlewoman has given inspiration to many through her high
21 ideals, morals, and deep concern for her fellow citizens, and she possesses the vast wisdom
22 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
23 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding contributions of this
25 exemplary veteran are appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 recognize and commend Kimia Irmesha Flournoy for the dedication, bravery, and sacrifices
28 she has made to serve her country and extend sincere best wishes for her continued health,
29 happiness, and success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Kimia Irmesha
32 Flournoy.
